website_summaries.verdict: A simple, classic wood design that fits in with contemporary decor. With several finishes, you can go from country to classic depending on your style.
pros: Simple design blends well with contemporary and traditional decor
cons: Aren't the most comfortable chairs to sit in

customer_reviews.title: These chairs were just what I was looking for!
customer_reviews.text: These chairs were perfect for my needs! I wanted 4 chairs to fit at the eat -in kitchen counter and these fit the bill/ No assembly, super solid, high quality, look very nice, and match my light oak kitchen. They are smaller than regular dining chairs, but everyone, from the 3 year old to the 52 year old, can sit in them comfortably. I'm attaching a picture to demonstrate the size difference. I'm very glad I bought them and would highly recommend to anyone looking to purchase chairs on the small side.
customer_reviews.author: Susan

customer_reviews.title: I like it!
customer_reviews.text: No assembly needed! I bought four chairs for this table:  and here is the result, I like it!
customer_reviews.author: Hengameh

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy chairs, great price
customer_reviews.text: These chairs are great. They come preassembled and are made of oak, a very sturdy wood. I had bought these chairs almost 4 years ago along with a set of 4 similar chairs for my kitchen table. The set of four fell apart but these chairs held up through many drunken parties and several large friends. I've just purchased 4 new ones of these chairs to replace the crappy other ones and they've arrived in perfect condition and are obviously the same as the old pair. I saw reviews about these being small, but I disagree. They're the right size for a Windsor chair. Love them and I hope to but some little cushions for them soon.
customer_reviews.author: M. Walker

customer_reviews.title: I bought a set on November 2015 and it is ...
customer_reviews.text: I bought a set on November 2015 and it is now August 2017. One of the chairs is going strong, but one of them has a part that's broken. You know that horizontal piece that connects the legs? Well, one of those broke on one of the chairs. I'm around 150 lbs., so that is surprising this early. I also find the back of the chair uncomfortable. I'm around 5'8" and the top of the back of the chair sits against my scapulae (i.e. shoulder blades).
customer_reviews.author: Muchy G

customer_reviews.title: Perfect fit for my kitchen!
customer_reviews.text: Sturdy. Good quality. Fast shipping. NO assembly. GREAT price. All four chairs fit easily under my kitchen table. I added felt floor protectors to prevent scratches. Perfect addition to my 1908 farmhouse kitchen!
customer_reviews.author: Loutre

customer_reviews.title: Bought as a gift
customer_reviews.text: We bought these as a gift to our son and DIL, to match the ones already around their kitchen table. Their family is growing and these extras really come in handy. We have the same chairs at home, and can attest that they are sturdy and well-made. Some folks like to add a chair pad, but I'm fine with the bare chair. For me, it's comfortable for an hour or more.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: These are nice chairs filing out the set of six I had.
customer_reviews.text: Since my Mom had a habit of grabbing a chair to stand on instead of a step ladder, she broke two of the set I had. So these are the same style, where the old ones have some white paint the new are all natural. I only wish Amazon offered the tack on floor savers for the bottom of the legs beside the purchase. These come bare wood. If you leave them, both the chairs and your floor will be in ruins. Over all they're a good buy.
customer_reviews.author: Paula - Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: Assembly is required
customer_reviews.text: The chairs were well packed, all necessary parts were in the box. The assembly directions are clear, but it would be helpful if the directions mentioned that glue was an option or to state explicitly that glue should not be used. Some additional directions, such as "do not tighten the cross pieces completely until the legs are completely seated" would be helpful. After assembly was completed the chairs were very solid. Looked good also. The angles chosen for the pre-drilled screw holes make it difficult to drive the screws in completely. I did think the ad stated that NO assembly would be required.
customer_reviews.author: Sandra Kohler

customer_reviews.title: Love the sturdiness of these chairs
customer_reviews.text: Love the sturdiness of these chairs, especially after the ones I purchased with a table set four years ago became super wobbly. While I've only had these for a couple of weeks, they are substantially sturdier and the price was good too. I like the double bars across the legs. Time will tell about any wobbling issues, but right now I'm extremely happy with these chairs.
customer_reviews.author: Nancy Donaldson

customer_reviews.title: Chairs will last less than 2 years, connectors break
customer_reviews.text: There is a reason this model was discontinued and upgraded with additional cross-bar in new model from same company. The connectors are weak and will break given enough time. The price for chairs that last only 2 years not great. Once the connectors break underneath, the chairs become immediately unstable. Might be the right look but the fact they did not last very long isn’t good. The wood is weak. Well within the weight restriction advertised. I think these chairs should be rated for maybe 100 pounds and be used as kid chairs based on the fractures I saw. Will have to keep eye out for similar chairs from different company. Buyer beware as they won’t last very long.
customer_reviews.author: Ewizard

customer_reviews.title: GREAT, IF YOU CAN FIT
customer_reviews.text: I love them. They are pretty sturdy, but you shouldn't have a wide butt. The side dowels are not set wide apart. They kind of wrap around the back of the seat, so a wide butt will have a hard time fitting all the way back in the chair. A skinny butt should fit fine.
customer_reviews.author: King'sCrown

customer_reviews.title: Bought 2 sets of 2 of the Winsome Wood Windsor Chair, Natural
customer_reviews.text: These chairs were bought to replace our old kitchen table chairs and the match was nearly 'Dead On' but Better Built, Slightly Larger (we wanted this) and REALLY the construction of the chairs makes the chairs feel better and stronger... We are very happy with this choice and the packaging was outstanding because the chairs were pack 2 to a box and there was no way that either chair would be able to make contact with the other during shipping. This Seller really knows what they are doing in all aspects of from buying to receiving these chairs. Very Happy with this product...
customer_reviews.author: Nick Rioux

customer_reviews.title: These chairs were good for what I needed
customer_reviews.text: These chairs were good for what I needed, which was two chairs to add to my dining set. They aren't fantastic quality, and they aren't the most comfortable things in the world, but they are definitely chairs. I can say that for 100% certain. If you sit in them, you will be sitting, and you will be sitting on them. Yep. There isn't much to say about these guys. They did come in very convenient packaging, no massive amounts of styrofoam or anything. If you need a quick pair of chairs, this is the right choice. If you are looking for a quality dining set, look elsewhere.
customer_reviews.author: Michael

customer_reviews.title: What just happened?
customer_reviews.text: I just received these chairs yesterday. I opened them and they are a great value for the $59.88 price I paid for them last week. I just ordered 2 because I wanted to be sure of the quality first. These appear to be very good quality. I went to order 2 more today and now they are $103 for a pair, instead of $59.88 for the pair! What just happened? Almost doubling in price in less than a week?
customer_reviews.author: D. Millar

customer_reviews.title: Exactly what we were looking for
customer_reviews.text: Perfect size for our small kitchen and sturdily built. Saw some chairs locally that were much wider and larger, but these are the perfect size for our 6 seater kitchen table. We have placed seat cushions on them that fit nicely. Look forward to years of use.
customer_reviews.author: K Griffee

customer_reviews.title: I love these chairs
customer_reviews.text: I love these chairs, they were a perfect fit and the price was so reasonable. The natural wood was a great match for my kitchen dining table which was still in great shape, but my chairs had seen better days, so this was a welcome and easy replacement of my old chairs.
customer_reviews.author: karen makeba

customer_reviews.title: Look nice, sturdiness is iffy.
customer_reviews.text: Good chairs. They almost match the set I have that needed a replacement chair. The weight limit said 220. I’m 180 and the legs wabbled under me when I sat. So, these will be the last chairs we sit in at the table.
customer_reviews.author: GBA

customer_reviews.title: Good sturdy chairs
customer_reviews.text: These are really good chairs for the price. I have owned several for years and they have held up. I recently needed to get a couple more and they were at a really good price. They have been sturdy and reliable for years at a really affordable price.
customer_reviews.author: Gary R.

customer_reviews.title: Nice looking but super good quality
customer_reviews.text: We have four of these chairs. We had to fix one of them by putting in place some falling parts (it worked). Still, we like them for their style. And they are comfy enough to be used as a desk chair. They came already assembled.
customer_reviews.author: Lise Krr

customer_reviews.title: Beautiful, affordable, assembled chairs!
customer_reviews.text: I love these chairs!!!! They arrived in beautiful condition and look perfect with my light wood butcher block table. They seem sturdy and well made. I have a relatively small kitchen area and the size is perfect. The looked pretty online and the fact that they came assembled sold me! They are perfect and I highly recommend them!
customer_reviews.author: Nancy Krinick

customer_reviews.title: Super Value
customer_reviews.text: These chairs are perfect for the price = Value! There are a couple of small cosmetic defects in the wood, but considering the price, I think they are minimal. I don't know of any other options to get this type chair for less than $50 each. I am so pleased that I am ordering two more- one for an office chair for my daughter and another as an extra kitchen table guest chair.
customer_reviews.author: Robert S.

customer_reviews.title: Comfortable height for elderly or persons with knee or back pain
customer_reviews.text: I purchased these chairs for my mother to replace two kitchen dinette chairs. The chair color matches the sellers photo, and the quality is sturdy and attractive and they arrived pre-assembled! We all love these chairs, I would buy these again!
customer_reviews.author: Amazonian

customer_reviews.title: These are very sturdy and reliable chairs
customer_reviews.text: These are very sturdy and reliable chairs. They aren't the prettiest but if you are looking in this price range than you know what you are looking at. Bargain priced products. And these deliver 100 percent if you realize that. Got 6 of them and they all arrived very well packaged and already assembled. That alone is worth a lot of money to me. I ABHOR any type of assembly process. These you take out of the box, take off the protective plastic., sit on them and enjoy your day. Highly recommend!
customer_reviews.author: David Y.

customer_reviews.title: These are nice chairs for the average adult
customer_reviews.text: These are nice chairs for the average adult. However I ordered them for someone who is shall be say more than average weight and they were rated for 300 lbs. NOT ! They are nicely made chairs, but don't believe the rating, it isn't accurate, plus they are tiny! The seat is very very small and almost any but the tiniest adult would be uncomfortable sitting in this chair for more than a few minutes. I rated them four stars for construction because they are constructed nicely for their size and good quality wood.
customer_reviews.author: J L W

customer_reviews.title: Excellent bargain. Buy with confidence
customer_reviews.text: I got these chairs for my wife's birthday and we are happy with them. We did have to return the first set due to some damage from shopping which was a total pain but Amazon didn't disappoint. We had the new set in no time. We've had them for a few years now and they are holding up greedy. The finish is holding strong and they look like new still (even with a toddler!). The price was great for new chairs. We usually buy our furniture used but the price point for new chairs was too good to pass up. The color looks just like the Amazon image.
customer_reviews.author: B_Mortimus

customer_reviews.title: Fantastic quality for price
customer_reviews.text: I bought theese chairs several years ago now for a table I actually found by my apartment dumpster. They arrived a week later two chairs per box fully assembled. They are very sturdy, and I think they are very comfortable for a wooden chair. I am a big guy (6ft 250) and have always felt stable in this chair. If I ever have need for more, I will certainly reorder these.
customer_reviews.author: Stafford

customer_reviews.title: Wobble, wobble
customer_reviews.text: Uneven legs on both chairs, instantly noticeable upon unpacking. Wobble back & forth when you try to sit. Given high ratings for these sturdy (looking) chairs, likely I received a bad pair, but...both chairs faulty, and not tested before shipping? Disappointing. Pre-assembled, good price, but back they go,
customer_reviews.author: KlearyT

customer_reviews.title: These chairs were a fine purchase and suit my needs quite well
customer_reviews.text: These chairs were a fine purchase and suit my needs quite well. They complement a light wood table I had for the dining area in my efficiency apartment. They are sturdy and well made. No assembly required was an added plus. The chairs arrived packaged in one unit, one chair on top of the other. The packaging provided enough padding so no damage in shipping occurred. These chairs are a good value for the money. I had visited thrift/consignment shops where the prices were more than 1.5 times the cost of these new chairs. I would purchase these chairs again for similar needs.
customer_reviews.author: Duffcapecod

customer_reviews.title: Look nice, but very flimsy.
customer_reviews.text: These chairs felt very light, but looked to have been decently constructed and had a smooth finish. Then they fell apart after a little over a month of use. Literally had the legs snap off. I'm not even that heavy! :C
customer_reviews.author: Sleepsteaks

customer_reviews.title: Good basic chairs
customer_reviews.text: These chairs seem sturdy. They arrived in one box and it wasn't very heavy, I could move it inside by myself. Both chairs had dried glue along the base of the pegs in the back - just sloppy craftsmanship. I'll chip it off. Otherwise they seem well made.
customer_reviews.author: nirvana91

customer_reviews.title: you get what you pay for....
customer_reviews.text: These arrived on time with packaging intact. I am very dismayed by the size and quality of these chairs. Previous reviews had clearly stated they would accommodate a 300 pound individual; however, there is a sticker on the bottom of the chair that says 220 limit! My larger family members are not impressed! There are many places on the chairs that are not varnished... so that will have to be done as well. You get what you pay for... and these are CHEAP chairs!
customer_reviews.author: NF JUDI

customer_reviews.title: Love these chairs.
customer_reviews.text: I received 2 sets of these chairs today. They were well packed and were not damaged in any way. The seats are big and comfortable and the correct height for our kitchen table. They have double rungs which many chairs do not have and are solid wood. They also match my cabinets. I am very well pleased.
customer_reviews.author: Charles R. McClatchy, Sr.

customer_reviews.title: Small chairs; not comfortable
customer_reviews.text: Smaller than I expected. Not easy to assemble even with the instructions in front of you. In my case, they will be used, when I got company, as extra chairs. I don't think they are comfortable enough for everyday use.
customer_reviews.author: ciprian cucu

customer_reviews.title: Wonderful Chairs!!
customer_reviews.text: These chairs are perfect! I have always wanted this style of chair for my kitchen and these do not disappoint. I have read some people feel these chairs are small but I find them to be 'normal' sized. I am 5'2" and when I sit in the chair my feet do not hit the floor completely. (This causes much hilarity for my darling twins.) One twin is almost 6' and the other is about 5'5. Both sit comfortably in these chairs. I don't have pads for them and I don't think I will get any as I find the chairs to be quite comfortable. (Whether I sit for a few minutes or a few hours.) Great buy!
customer_reviews.author: River

customer_reviews.title: We have just 3 months of use on them but I can tell they're going to be around for a happy long life
customer_reviews.text: Arrived on time, were very well assembled and they're just so solid and cheerful with generous seating space. We have just 3 months of use on them but I can tell they're going to be around for a happy long life.
customer_reviews.author: L. A.

customer_reviews.title: The chairs are super strong and go with any theme at all
customer_reviews.text: The chairs are super strong and go with any theme at all. I'd recommend to anyone, especially if you have a large, robust family. For the price, I'd suggest sending to Grandma's house before showing up with your family of six for Christmas. In fact, a couple as hostess guests would make you Welcome at parties. They are truly wonderful and I'm so happy I've found them. They come two chairs to a box, well packed, and easy enough for me to move around and unpack. Little trash, most of the packing material was recyclable in my rural area.
customer_reviews.author: Candy Ryan

customer_reviews.title: Solid, good looking
customer_reviews.text: Arrived in perfect condition, assembled. Very solid...stood on one to put up decorations, level and well-made. Finish is good. Nice additions to my dining room table. Well worth price.
customer_reviews.author: L. Chapin

customer_reviews.title: They are what they say they are!
customer_reviews.text: I ordered six chairs and they arrived promptly. As others have commented, they were packed well and were not difficulty to unpack. I used these chairs for Thanksgiving. They fit well under my antique table and were suitable for smaller to larger people. The chairs are solid. I am very happy with the purchase I am ordering more without hesitation.
customer_reviews.author: tooretac

customer_reviews.title: Good cheap replacement kitchen chairs
customer_reviews.text: I have had these chairs since March. We needed to replace old chairs. These matched the table. They came assembled in sets of 2. These are what they are. They are adequate for what we wanted. If you are looking for extremely high end quality these are not that. They have held up well so far. If you simply want a reasonable replacement for little money these are that.
customer_reviews.author: Joseph H. Allen

customer_reviews.title: Love Them ~
customer_reviews.text: I love the color of the chairs, the Natural wood is just georgous. They arrived very quickly, were very well packaged & put together, they arrived UPS, Out of the box & ready for us to sit. The smooth finish is perfect, I was a little leary based on prior reviews of them being to small but they are normal size. We are awaiting delivery of our new kitchen table so we will have true use later this week. With Free Shipper Saver, Fast Delivery and the exact color we were searching for, these chairs can not be beat! Thank You for making them avaliable.
customer_reviews.author: Super Shopper

customer_reviews.title: Windsor Chairs... for Kids
customer_reviews.text: These chairs are correctly sized for children, not adults. Visually they appear to be about 70% of the size of the chairs in my dining room set. Thankfully, I was buying them for my kids, but your needs may vary.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Perfect fit
customer_reviews.text: Great chairs. Almost match or regular chairs that we use daily. Sturdy, well built. Very happy with product. We liked the chairs so much we ordered 8 more for the holidays and special occasions.
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: Chairs came assembled
customer_reviews.text: These chairs arrived promptly and came fully assembled. I was so thrilled to get them! They are fairly heavy and seem sturdy. I have noticed that the furniture that we assemble does not seem to hold up as well as furniture that is already assembled, but its so hard to find an item that is reasonably priced and comes assembled. I hope I can find some other things that come assembled, but regardless, I am well pleased with these chairs. They look very good, are heavy and seem sturdy. I love them, so far.
customer_reviews.author: Louise Angel

customer_reviews.title: Excellent buy, matches our 12 year old Winsome table ...
customer_reviews.text: Excellent buy, matches our 12 year old Winsome table and chairs. Slightly smaller than our existing chairs but still a good match. If you need chairs this is a safe buy. Highly recommended!
customer_reviews.author: J Hess

customer_reviews.title: Still look great after years of use
customer_reviews.text: I've had these chairs almost 4 years now. They sit at each end of my studio for guitar players and used often. They have held up well and the finish still looks great. Still tight as the day they arrived. Very pleasantly surprised.
customer_reviews.author: M D McCallum

customer_reviews.title: I'd buy again. Good quality, good price.
customer_reviews.text: Purchased a couple, then a couple more, then 2 more. They are of decent quality and work great to replace chairs at our casual dining table. I would buy more if I needed them but the first ones I purchase are now a year old and still excellent. Pay attention to the delivery date, because one pair I ordered did take several weeks to arrive (like it stated it would). The others were quicker to arrive.
customer_reviews.author: Hap Hazzard

customer_reviews.title: Love 'em so far
customer_reviews.text: Love 'em so far. Very well constructed ! BTW -- I went out and bought some white rubber chair leg tips. which is certainly appreciated for our linoleum floor. Brand is Shepherds. Size is Inch and an Eighth Fits PERFECTLY ! Sit on the chair, after installation, to make sure the rubber tips are Firmly seated.
customer_reviews.author: Hugh Manatee

customer_reviews.title: Nice casual kitchen chair
customer_reviews.text: I purchased these to match an oak set that had 4 chairs but needed a few more. They match perfectly.
customer_reviews.author: Mrs.D

customer_reviews.title: I am really pleased with these and highly recommend them
customer_reviews.text: A while I back I learned my lesson about reviewing a product as soon as you get it, so I waited until I had these for a bit before reviewing. First of all it is a huge plus they come put together already and the packaging wasn't too ridiculous to get through. I was worried shipping might loosen glue to whatever but the chairs have held up, it's been a month or so. I am really pleased with these and highly recommend them.
customer_reviews.author: Ashley Jarosi

customer_reviews.title: Pretty Nice
customer_reviews.text: I like how these chairs look and they shipped quickly too. However they are not super sturdy as most furniture made these days isn't either. The weight limit is stated at 250 lbs but my chair has gotten a wobbly leg after a few short weeks of use. I am well under the max weight and am a fairly gentle person. If you are light and gentle these are nice chairs but if you are a little on the heavy side and yank your chair out and slam your butt onto the seat these are not a good choice.
customer_reviews.author: Kim E

customer_reviews.title: Good Chairs
customer_reviews.text: I bought these to replace my old set (8+ years old) which I was tired of gluing back together. The construction on these chairs appears to be excellent. All of the joints were reinforced with screws, so no worries about the chair falling apart underneath you and no gluing in my future! The finish is good, though there were a few spots that weren't "perfectly" smooth. The wood was a darker color than I was expecting, but I'm pleased overall with the chair's quality and construction.
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: A real bargain!
customer_reviews.text: Honestly expected less for the price. Attractive, sturdy, and fully assembled. Our kids could break boulders, dipped in cast iron, with a diamond hardened finish! But these chairs have defied their destructive efforts! And look and feel like we paid twice as much as we did.
customer_reviews.author: JimofSalem

customer_reviews.title: Excellent - Highly recommend
customer_reviews.text: Excellent chairs! So happy with these. I should have written a review right away but I've been too busy enjoying the chairs with my new table.
customer_reviews.author: Nechama

customer_reviews.title: Chair broken when delivered
customer_reviews.text: One of the chairs arrived broken. The leg was broken close to where it connects to the seat. From the looks of the box, someone dropped it because there was a puncture hole. Most likely, it was the shipper. Rather than go through the hassle of returning it, I taped it, inserted a screw and a clamp. Otherwise, they are OK. The quality is about average. There is not much curvature for your back and the seat is hard. You get what you pay for. We will probably keep these a while and look for something better.
customer_reviews.author: FJ

customer_reviews.title: Chairs worked out great for us.
customer_reviews.text: The chairs are perfect. They are sturdier than the ones we've had for 16 years. They are a little bit smaller than our older ones, but that's okay. It's nice to not have to worry about loose legs or the backing any more.
customer_reviews.author: J S G 57

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy!
customer_reviews.text: I purchased these based on all those wonderful Amazon.com reviews. I love the chairs - the price was right - much less than sold for in the big box stores and the quality is great. Delivery was prompt - came in one very large box and best of all - No Assembly Required. Actually, I like this chair style much better than the ones that came with my kitchen set. Now lets see how long it takes my visiting grandchildren to destroy these - that will be the real test! If they manage to do so at this price, I'll just buy two more.
customer_reviews.author: KokoMe

customer_reviews.title: Excellent Quality
customer_reviews.text: Perfect chairs to go with farmhouse style kitchen. Ordered pair and intended to order 2nd pair only to see price increased. Guess we will get along with only one pair!
customer_reviews.author: Dulcigran

customer_reviews.title: Perfect for my small dining area!
customer_reviews.text: This set of chairs is sturdy and works perfect for my dining area in my small apartment. I bought them to go with a farm type table and bench that my daughter gave me when I moved into my apartment and they match the table perfectly and made a huge difference in how my dining area looks. Granted, they are not large chairs for a large dining set but with care, they should last me for a long time. I would recommend them to others.
customer_reviews.author: Marie Alline

customer_reviews.title: Cheap price, cheaper quality
customer_reviews.text: Cheap price, even cheaper quality. Loose joints, uneven spindles and Brad nails with no glue at support points. If I keep these I will disassemble and reassemble with proper glueing techniques. Should have spent more money on higher quality chairs. No more furniture purchases from Amazon.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: I ordered these chairs because of the great reviews. I made a mistake by letting my ...
customer_reviews.text: I ordered these chairs because of the great reviews. I made a mistake by letting my kids play with the shipping box (and they basically destroyed it). So, when the chairs started to wobble after about a week (nobody even close to the weight limit used the chairs) I have the issue of finding a box big enough to return them. I would strongly advise that, if you buy these chairs, you save the box for a few weeks to make sure they aren't junk.
customer_reviews.author: Raymond J Van Severen

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy
customer_reviews.text: These chairs are very sturdy. I ordered them to replace the chairs for my kitchen table. I have a natural wood colored butcher block table. The chairs match it perfectly. The chairs I had after 8 years had become wobbly and somewhat scary to sit on. They felt like they were going to fall apart under you. But these are very sturdy and though they look like the chairs I used to have, they feel much better made then the original chairs that came with the table.
customer_reviews.author: Cheri

customer_reviews.title: The one good thing I can say about these chairs is that ...
customer_reviews.text: I ordered these chairs because I have 4 of the exact same brand that we use right now. Ours now have been used and abused and have served us for a long time. It was time to order more so I picked these. The one good thing I can say about these chairs is that they feel pretty solid. The height of the chair is the same as our old ones but the seat part is tiny! Also, a couple of them don't sit level with the floor. Needless to say, I will be returning them.
customer_reviews.author: Sara

customer_reviews.title: They have a great finish on them and are as pictured
customer_reviews.text: These chairs are much sturdier than expected for the price. They arrived quickly in a fairly large box and were packaged well to prevent damage. They have a great finish on them and are as pictured. My husband thinks they are smaller than regular chairs but I disagree with this statement. They fit my table well and do not seem smaller than they should be for the table.
customer_reviews.author: Kendra

customer_reviews.title: Good-quality, inexpensive chairs.
customer_reviews.text: Nice little chairs. Well built. They come all assembled, two in a box (I bought two sets). I was pleasantly surprised by the good-quality finish. You can't go wrong for that price.
customer_reviews.author: Francois

customer_reviews.title: Look and feel great. Easy!
customer_reviews.text: I am so happy with these chairs! This review might sound fake because I'm so happy with them, but who would write a fake reviews for chairs? That would be a little weird. I bought these chairs to replace much older ones that had become too wobbly to fix. These arrived on time and fully assembled. They look and feel great. They are sturdy! After years of trying to fix and tighten my old chairs, I had to laugh when I sat in these. They are perfect and buying them was so easy. I should have bought them years ago!
customer_reviews.author: kelly keefe

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy chairs  | Well packed
customer_reviews.text: Bought a pair of these for last Thanksgiving then bought 6 more for this Thanksgiving. They are well made and come well packed fully assembled. Recommend getting Magic Sliders to put on the feet.
customer_reviews.author: W. Kriebel

customer_reviews.title: nice, but take care
customer_reviews.text: I order from Amazon all the time. I needed these chairs for extra seating in my kitchen. Saw these, price was great and they are similar to what I already had. They came with good packing and in a timely manner, but one chair must have been defective because the first time an adult (under 200 lbs) sat on it, she crashed to the floor. One of the legs had split near the seat. Other chair is fine. So, test carefully before you use!!
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: Replacement chairs that work
customer_reviews.text: very nice and sturdy chairs. I bought them to compliment a rectangular European style kitchen table in a bay window. They lend an airy look to the space. If you plan to sit longer than a meal takes, you might need to buy chair pads.

customer_reviews.title: Great Value!
customer_reviews.text: Very well constructed. No creaking or wobble. Very solid feel when sitting down, yet light enough to scoot on the floor. The finish on the chairs was quality, no lines or drips. I would have to pay much more for these in the furniture stores.

customer_reviews.title: Good solid chairs!
customer_reviews.text: Good solid chairs! The bow back is splined and screwed into the chair seat; the legs are screwed into the seat as well. Just a nice looking chair without the especially fine finish found in some furniture stores. I just added felt pads to the legs. You may want to add chair pads for comfort. My chairs arrived well protected and without defects.

customer_reviews.title: Everything I expected!
customer_reviews.text: My mother needed replacement chairs so I had ordered these for her after reading such good reviews. They came on time as they said they would come, they came all put together so no there was no hassle on putting them together, they are sturdy chairs and she is completely happy and satisfied with her purchase! She is ordering two more chairs! The backs are just a TAD shorter than her original chairs but they actually work out MUCH better for her since her kitchen space is small. All in all, great service, great product and I would definitely suggest to a friend!
customer_reviews.author: Lisa

customer_reviews.title: Please be seated, you will enjoy the experience.
customer_reviews.text: The price appeared to be reasonable for a couple of pedestrian chairs so I took a chance and was well rewarded. They arrived fully assembled (joy,oh joy) well packed and in perfect condition and, by golly, they are actually attractive! Add to that the fact that my wife and I find them surprisingly comfortable. And finally, there also is a pleasurable sturdiness about them that we truly appreciate. Huzzah, huzzah--we picked a winner!

customer_reviews.title: and they are great. No signs of coming apart

customer_reviews.title: On th small side.
customer_reviews.text: I purchased these chairs to match missing chairs in a kitchen set. I didn't realize they would be so much smaller than the ones we were replacing. On the up side, we now comfortably fit 8 seats around the table with ease. On the down side, they are noticeably smaller than the arm chairs at the ends of the table. On the plus side they are well constructed and sturdy. They are comfortable for an average person and will accommodate smaller settings.

customer_reviews.text: thank you amazon. you saved me alot of money and headache. after hitting 12 local furniture stores looking for decent chairs for our christmas gathering instead of folder, I found these. 2 arrived 2 days after ordering with free shipping. excellent. these chairs are larger than the folding wood beach chairs what we had with our nice blond beech wood dutch leaf extension table in our sunroom. these are not 2XL chairs, maybe closer to a Large, very satisfied, I ordered 4 and 2 showed up promptly, the other 2 are on their way....and I just now ordered 2 more for a total of 6. assembled in USA from imported materials..decent packaging.....as good as it can get...A+ win win [...]

customer_reviews.title: Great price for the quality
customer_reviews.text: They are rugged but the bottoms of the feet are not cut flat to the floor. So I had to level them to add felt pads. Great price for the quality.
customer_reviews.author: Norman

customer_reviews.title: Great product - FAST delivery
customer_reviews.text: I ordered 2 sets (4 chairs) on a Saturday night and they arrived in RI on Tuesday! Well packed and well made. No assembly, no wobbling. The color is as shown in the picture and they match my old butcher block table perfectly. I read the comments about the chairs being "small" but that's certainly relative. The height is the same as my old chairs, but the seat is a bit narrower. I actually like the look of these better since when compared to what I had, the old ones actually look too wide. These fit around the table better too. I'm 6'-1" and 190 lbs. No issues with them being uncomfortable or small.
customer_reviews.author: Chris

customer_reviews.title: As Expected
customer_reviews.text: Saw reviews complaining about the comfort and durability of these chairs, and so far they are just fine. They arrived assembled, match and fit well with a 36" table I stained natural, and have held up to my 250 lb husband as well as my 2-year-old tipping them over. Don't expect luxury, but for the price they are good little chairs. My only complaint is after they arrived and I decided I liked them enough to buy another 2, the price had gone up by $30.
customer_reviews.author: kmac

customer_reviews.title: Sturdy kitchen chairs with stress-free shipping
customer_reviews.text: We ordered this product, because it matched our 4 dining room chairs and we recently purchased a larger table that sat 6. The chairs matched in color and quality. We especially enjoyed the price of the product and the free shipping. The chairs arrived promptly and were packed extremely carefully to avoid damage during transport. I was concerned about shipping furniture, but found that the completely assembled product arrived without any incident directly to my door. Now we have a complete set to our table and you would never know we didn't purchase all 6 together or from different stores in different years.
customer_reviews.author: Carol Foster

customer_reviews.title: I weigh 125 pounds and I am 5'1" and I find the chair to be very comfortable without a cushion
customer_reviews.text: Chairs came already assembled and don't wobble! I weigh 125 pounds and I am 5'1" and I find the chair to be very comfortable without a cushion.

I came home from work, opened the box (while hearing my wife complain how she had to drag the box into the house, gotta love her), pull the chairs out, sit in them and sigh. If I ever buy a grand table I will be sure to buy 2 or 4 more of these chairs..

product_meta.title: Winsome Wood Windsor Seating, Natural
product_meta.description: This classic style Windsor chair is built from solid wood providing great quality along with it timeless design. The round legs and smooth contoured seat gives it an exquisite traditional look which is also comfortable to sit on. The chair is 17. 25"W x 16. 5"D x 37"H with a seat Height of 17. 9" And Dimensions of 18. 5"W x 15. 4"D. The seat back is 19. 2"W x 18. 1"H and the chair has a weight capacity of 220 lbs. Comes fully assembled.
feature_bullets: Set of 2 classic Windsor chairs for use at the dinner table from Winsome Wood
Crafted in solid beech wood with double-rung stretchers between legs for sturdy foundation; natural finish
Hoop frame and spindles for back support; 17-inch high seat holds up to 220 pounds
